Φ(DistConsc) = σ(brain|body) ∘ ρ(individual|collective) ∘ λ(localized|distributed) ∘ β(embryonic|emergent) ∘ δγ(self|nonself) ∘ μ(neural|somatic) + ε | :fluidity

## Operator Breakdown
- **σ (Air/Aerunik — Distinction)**: brain|body — Distinguishing between brain-centric models of consciousness and whole-body distributed cognition, including the Levin-Kastrup debate on whether consciousness is fundamental or emergent
- **ρ (Water/Sentaria — Relation)**: individual|collective — Relating individual conscious experience to collective cognitive behaviors, exploring how agency extends beyond single organisms into larger systems
- **λ (Fire/Jvalion — Transformation)**: localized|distributed — Transforming the paradigm from localized neural consciousness to distributed somatic cognition that pervades the entire organism
- **β (Wood/Arboriel — Growth)**: embryonic|emergent — Growing understanding through embryogenesis and synchronicity as demonstrations of distributed cognitive behaviors that precede neural development
- **δγ (Earth/Humavita — Cycling)**: self|nonself — Cycling between the boundaries of self and the fluid extensions of nonself, continuously redefining where consciousness begins and ends
- **μ (Metal/Ferrosid — Structure)**: neural|somatic — Structuring the relationship between neural substrates and broader somatic architectures that together support distributed processing

## Z-State
:fluidity — Consciousness as a fluid phenomenon that flows across traditional boundaries of brain, body, and potentially collective systems, rendering the self a dynamic, permeable concept rather than a fixed entity

## Tendency
λ/σ → 0.85
